parameters:
\nw[\N[21]]Should I try talking to the woman who is
commanding those soldiers...

\nw[Conductor]I wonder why those three are still alive after
that injury?

\nw[Female Commander]Oh, what brings all of you here...? Do you need
something from me?

\nw[\N[21]]It's not like I have a specific purpose, but I was
just wondering why you brought soldiers to a place
like this.

\nw[Female Commander]Hehehe... You've come from afar, haven't you?
We're here because violent monsters have appeared
in the west, and we're going to exterminate them.

\nw[Female Commander]...Oh? Aren't you the mercenaries from Dios? And
those two women over there too.

\nw[\N[21]](Can you tell just by looking...? The citizens of
Dios and Misura may look similar, but...)

\nw[Female Commander]What are you doing in a place like this? The
relationship between Dios and our country isn't
exactly friendly, you know.

\nw[\N[21]]Ah... I was hired by the owner of this country's
mercenary group and ended up working as a
mercenary in this country. This time, I'm heading
to Rimurun for a job.

\nw[\N[21]]Also, I obtained the citizenship of this country,
so technically I have become a citizen of this
country.

\nw[Female Commander]Is that so? Hehe, I'm sorry. I just got a little
curious because there have been some suspicious
movements from the Dios side.

\nw[\N[21]]No, it's okay. I'm \N[21], the leader of the
mercenary group NTR in the pleasure city of Solte.
\nw[Female Commander]Thank you very much. As for me... well...

\nw[Female Commander]I'll introduce myself using my nickname since it's
more well-known than my real name. I am Conductor.
I have the honor of serving as Aegis No. II of the
country of Misura.

\nw[Conductor]Well, I'm not as strong as the other Aegis. My
main role is mostly in the rear.

\nw[Conductor]I'm quite aware that I'm well-known due to my
appearances in public relations, but it seems like
you didn't know.

\nw[\N[21]]Ah, ah... Sorry, it hasn't been much time since I
obtained my citizenship.

\nw[Conductor]If you're a mercenary, it would be wise to
remember the face and name of an Aegis. It could
be troublesome if we end up on opposing sides in a
job.

\nw[Conductor]Well, even though I don't show my face about half
the time...

\nw[\N[21]]Ah, well, I'll try my best not to become enemies
with you.
\nw[Conductor]Hehe... It would be helpful if you could do that.

\nw[Conductor]So, you're heading towards Rimuru, huh? In that
case, you're already quite close.
\nw[Conductor]If you go north, you'll arrive soon.

\nw[\N[21]]Is that so? Thank goodness. Well then, I'll
depart.

\nw[\N[3]]Probably. I feel like I recognize the woman at the
front...

\nw[Dalton]If you're curious, why don't you try talking to
them? As the leader of the mercenary group, it's
good to have a wide network.
\nw[\N[21]]Yeah, why not give it a try and talk to them.
There is no need to go any further.
There is no need to go any further.

\nw[Shia]Thank you. Thanks to you, the live ended as a
great success.

\nw[\N[21]]Ah, I'm glad I could be of help. So, you're coming
to my place to speed up the curse's lifting,
right? Are you not coming together?

\nw[Shia]Sorry, there are still things I need to take care
of. Well, I'll come after I finish, so please wait
for me.

\nw[\N[21]]Alright, I understand. But are you sure it's okay?
Won't it be exposed to the public that you're
being treated by a man?

\nw[Shia]What kind of image do you have of me inside your
mind? I'm not exactly the innocent type, am I?
There's no one who has such dreams about me.

\nw[Shia]So don't worry about it. I've never been a
mercenary or a sex worker, so I'm looking forward
to it.

\nw[\N[21]]Alright, I got it. I'll wait for you at Solte. See
you later.
